Of Bertoxxulous <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elyta>Elyta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/14/02 10:38:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Area effect spells</span><hr size=1> If, when you say good crowd control, you mean if you have an enchanter... then DO NOT USE AOE AT ALL!!! PLEASE!!!<br>
<br>
AoE breaks Mez (well except the colour stuns)<br>
<br>
Do NOT AoE around mezzed creatures please!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukrugal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krugal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/14/02 11:44:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Area effect spells</span><hr size=1> That I knew, I was referring to snared or rooted monsters,<br>
<br>
Krugal<br>
Gnome Wizard<br>
Of Bertoxxulous <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elyta>Elyta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/14/02 2:18:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Area effect spells</span><hr size=1> Sorry then, but it can't be said enough, and it doesnt stop with idiots who AoE. The number of times people say they are fine with playing alongside enchanters and then:<br>
<br>
- AoE around mezzed mobs<br>
- DoT mobs<br>
- Main tanks changing targets to &quot;rescue&quot; the enchanter<br>
- Not use /assist<br>
<br>
etc.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukrugal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krugal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/14/02 4:28:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Area effect spells</span><hr size=1> No problem, but whats wrong with changing target to rescue the enchanter? Used to play a warrior and did this sometimes, was it wrong, and if so why?<br>
<br>
Krugal<br>
Gnome Wizard<br>
Of Bertoxxulous <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=samildanach>Samildanach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/17/02 1:09:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Area effect spells</span><hr size=1> The rule about not AE nuking when you are grouped with an enchanter is generally a good one to follow for most of your career. <br>
<br>
Right now your AE spells may seem a bit weak and liable to get you killed but hold on in there if you can because they get better, much better <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Although it's true you won't be able to use them freely in a &quot;normal&quot; group, if you have the right group composition and open-minded groupmates it will be possible to use your area effect damage spells to tremendous effect at later levels in an &quot;AE group&quot;. AE groups work differently to the standard way of doing things. Usually, if your puller brings in several monsters, the enchanter will mez them and the group will kill them one at a time. In AE groups however, it generally goes something like this:<br>
<br>
1. Your puller DELIBERATELY rounds up a large group of monsters and brings them to the group, the more the better. In effect, he pulls a train. The puller will need to bring at least 4 monsters in order for your AE nukes to be mana efficient and pulls of 20 or more monsters are quite common in this type of group.<br>
<br>
2. This is where people who've never seen an AE group before freak out. Instead of mezzing all the monsters your enchanter will instead step in amongst them and continuously cast his 3 &quot;color&quot; stun spells, one after the other. These are point-blank area effect spells, capable of stunning an unlimited number of targets surrounding the enchanter. Your enchanter will generally need to be at least 44th level to do this properly because only then will he have all 3 stun spells he needs to keep the monsters &quot;stun locked&quot; - constantly stunned and unable to move (trying this with an enchanter lower than 44th is possible but risky).<br>
<br>
3. While the enchanter is keeping all the monsters stunned, everyone with point-blank area effect spells stands close to him and lets loose with them and you kill all the monsters in one go. You have to use point-blank AE spells here to do the damage because only they can hit an unlimited number of targets. Rain and Column spells are no good (they can only hit a few targets).<br>
<br>
And that's it.<br>
<br>
The key to it all is that your AE nukes will NOT break stun like they would mez and you need to chose your opponents carefully because all it takes is a couple of resists on the stuns to interupt your enchanter's casting and the group will die within seconds if all the monsters become unstunned at once. Generally groups will start off small, pulling only a few monsters at first until they've gotten used to things before making bigger and bigger pulls.<br>
<br>
But don't let the risk of death put you off when you are high enough to consider it. It is a high risk but also high reward strategy (the xp can be fantastic) and far more fun than the usual one-at-a-time style of fighting <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
This is generally a high level (50+ ) strategy but something to look forward to. The experience can be quite amazing and once you've tried it I guarantee you'll be hooked. The problem comes in finding people who are willing to try it and then finding an area with enough monsters to kill  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=stavehamvaliant>StavehamValiant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/27/02 1:39:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Area effect spells</span><hr size=1> For the longest time, I resisted using AoE spells, as all the mobs would aggro me. Seemed better to assist the tank and DD the mob once or twice. I almost forgot the joy of AoE spells. <br>
<br>
Well, recently, two groups of us went to the live side of Lower Guk. And we did very well. (9 of us total, group of 4, group of 5). And for the first time, I got to use AoE's and not pull aggro, or burn up mana one mob at a time. I waited till the fighting and gone on long enough. We didn't focus all nine players on one mob (but when we enchoutered one mob all alone, wandering around guk, they had a very short life). <br>
<br>
I stood far way from the main fighting. With that many players around, there was more then enough close by targets to hold each mobs attention. And I let loose an AoE spell. <br>
<br>
The joy I felt of hitting 5 mobs, three times each for 128 damage each time was wonderful. And not one mob came after me. That figures to about 1920 points of collective damage for 200 mana. <br>
<br>
Adds? Well, I waited till the fighting had gone on for some time before I cast the Lava storm. Any adds we were going to get, had happened by that time. So I wasn't worried about causing any.<br>
<br>
I also think there was a degree of luck behind it as well. It could have easily turned out to be the wrong thing to do. The more people there are around you, the better these spells seem to work. And more effective to. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uenheduannalia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EnheduannaLia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/27/02 4:14:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Area effect spells</span><hr size=1> I'd like to thank Samildanach for an excellent overview of the classic AoE group. I wish I'd seen something like that prior to my first AoE group! There we were, on the ledge of Velks, the warrior pulling huge trains and me thinking we are all going to die. But we didn't, and it was quite a thrill. Not to mention good exp. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
There's another AoE group that I, as a magician, really like. Mage + Shaman = limitless mana and terrific AoE duo. It could work with a wizard, too, but you'd have to watch your mana carefully. When we did it, I was OOM before very many beasties had died, but I just used mod rods to regain mana while the shaman kept me healed (and I gave back the mana, too). Rod, nuke, repeat until all dead. Well, we let my pet finish off the stragglers. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Oh yes, how does that duo work? Shaman rounds up the mobs by slowing four at a time, bringing them into a nice group. This was usually done while I was medding to get the last bit of mana, with a mod rod ready for use. Then I step into the middle, let pet hit whatever it wants while I chain cast pbAoE. Shaman keeps them slowed to limit the damage I take, and he keeps healing me with torpor. I use mod rods, as I mentioned above, when mana gets low. You need to have a lot of trust between both parties of the duo. <p><p align=center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=237657><b>Enheduanna Lia</b></a>, Arch Mage<br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucatafv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cataFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Firemunchkin</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/29/02 4:26:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=103.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.bigpond.net.au/stbt/sigs/redwizard2.gif height=60 width=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Area effect spells</span><hr size=1> I happen to know a friendly shaman... we are now 29 (me) and 25 (him).  At what rank would we start to make an efficient hunting team?  Cause we tried hunting together a little while ago, but our skills didn't seem to mesh that well yet. <p><center>
