<br>
/shudder...<br>
<br>
Nothing if you are a warrior and you change target and hit taunt only.  But don't melee it, as you may instabreak a successfully channelled mezz.<br>
<br>
If you are a rogue/monk and you switch targets you will KILL the enchanter.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Transcript of post I did on my guild boards for guidance:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
Hi all, I realise I am not the most patient of individuals at times, so bear with me here.  I am totally unsure of the relative experience of people in the guild so I don’t know who it is acceptable to shout at for breaking mezz when they shouldn’t or who to give more leeway too.<br>
To this end, as it may not be something everyone is comfortable with, I thought I’d put down some guidelines here for how to make enchanters happy (and not get them and yourselves killed as much!)<br>
<br>
Thanks for listening,<br>
<br>
Inconnu<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Key Roles:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Main Tank<br>
Any other melee<br>
Healers<br>
Other people with crowd control skillz<br>
Snare Classes<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Main Tank:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Basically there are a few important things here from a chanter perspective.<br>
Rule 1: Before breaking mezz on a mezzed mob make sure you hit taunt twice.  This should generally help to ensure that it doesn’t come tearing after me the instant mezz breaks. <br>
Rule 2: Create a hotbutton called ‘TARGET’ with the following command on the first line:<br>
/g [ %T ] is targeted. Please assist me in killing it<br>
Whenever you target a new mob, taunt twice, autoattack on (immediately if not mezzed, after taunt if mezzed) and then hit this button.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Other melees:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Create a hotbutton called:  MAINTANK<br>
On line one add the following text: (replace Kozz with whoever is main tank on raid/group)<br>
/assist Kozz<br>
You should stand about waiting for the Main Tank to call a target.  When called, hit your MAINTANK button to target the correct mob.  This ensures you get the correct one if there are multiples mobs with the same name. Then sidle over to mob and hit autoattack.  If you aren’t hitting the mob, its because you are looking at the wrong mob, there is 90% likely another mob with the same name which is the one you should be hitting.  Take a good look around, locate prey and move over to it.  Whatever you do, do not target mobs by left clicking them, always use the assist button.<br>
<br>
Oh and there's no need to tell everyone you are assisting Kozz with another line of text!! Not interested! I trust you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Healers:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Your job is to keep people alive, that includes the chanter!  Bear in mind that chanter hp/acs suck. Don’t let a chanter wander about at 50% health.  The moment their health bar starts to move down, slam a fast heal on them, we die fast!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Other people with crowd control skillz:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
