<br>
Circumstance one: lots of adds, clerics and chanters getting railed on.<br>
If you don’t have root or mezz, you might still be able to help:<br>
<br>
Rogue/Monks/Pets – You can help in one way only, get on with killing the mob that was called by the main tank.  You don’t have taunt, if you break mezz it will take you a while to get agro. In which time, the mezzer will be more likely to have succeeded in mezzing if you haven’t wailed in there and started trying to own the mob!<br>
<br>
Melee classes with TAUNT, you can taunt mobs off the clerics / chanters / overnuking wizzies, don’t use melee, just taunt them to get their attention, until someone can mezz or root the beauties. As soon as you have them beating on you, switch back to helping kill the mob the main tank is targeting and ignore them.  <br>
<br>
