<br>
The earilest useful type of AoE is your Column/Pillar line.  This is a targeted AoE (which means you cast it on a target at range just like a spell) and can hit up to 4 targets in a very small area.  You get your first column at level 16.  This line of spells is used most often in Quad Kiting but can also be used at certain levels for grouping.<br>
<br>
The next type of AoE you'll be likely to use is your rain line. This is another targeted AoE line. This line of spells really is not effecient until level 52 when you get to your Tears spells.  This line of spells will cause up to 3 &quot;rains&quot; that will hit a maximum of 4 times total.  If one critter is caught in the AoE, it will be hit 3 times.  If two are caught, they will each be hit twice.  If three or four are caught, they will each be hit once.  This is mainly used in groups because it is effecient, even on a single target.  Basically it acts like a 18 second DoT with the caveat that if the mob moves out of the AoE radius, you &quot;lose&quot; damage, and the mob can resist each wave independantly.  Typically with the Tears line, you need to hit 2 of the 3 waves to be more effecient than your normal DDs.<br>
<br>
The third type of AoE is your Point Blank (or player based) AoE.  These AoEs radiate out from yourself rather than radiate out from your target, and you cannot be hit by them.  The advantage to them is that they can hit an unlimited number of targets.  This is the AoE that you use in AoE groups.<br>
<br>
A fourth AoE type is a variant on the PBAoE which adds a stun to the AoE.<br>
<br>
The final type of wizard AoE is the Al'Kabor line of spells which are like our Pillar line, but hit one more target in a bit larger area for WAY more mana.  Even hitting a max of 5 targets, this AoE is NOT mana effecient and most regard this line of spells as a utter and complete waste of a spell book slot.<br>
<br>
For more information on how to Quad, when to use Rains in groups, when to use AoE in standard exp groups, how to do an AoE group, etc, hop on over to www.graffe.com.  It's basically the de-facto wizard site and you'll find most everything in its Forums section.<br>
<br>
AoE spells, espeically 50, are the wizards single most effecient way to deal damage.  Ignoring them or putting them away just because there's a chanter in your group is really hamstringing your potential.  Learn when, where, and how to use those AoE spells and people will be amazed by what you're able to do.<br>
<br>
Just as an example...<br>
<br>
Your draught line of spells are the most effecient DD spells you will get until Ice Spear of the Solist at level 60.  Those spells weigh in between 3.16 and 3.4 Hps dealth per mana point used.<br>
<br>
Tears of Druzzil, your level 52 rain, does 600 DD per wave for 380 mana.  If two of your three waves hit, that's 3.16 Damage per mana.  If three of your waves hit, that's 4.7 Damage per mana.  If, through tank splitting rather than mezzing on a two pull, you get four of your waves to hit, that's 2,400 damage for 380 mana or a 6.3 Damage per mana ratio.  That's better than alot of DoTs out there, and the total time to deal that damage is 12 seconds.  That's basically the equavelent of doing an Ice Comet to two mobs for less mana that it takes to cast an Ice Comet on a single mob.  No other class is gonna pump out that kind of damage that fast at level 52 for that little mana.<br>
<br>
Wizard AoE spells can get to staggering mana effeciencies.  The highest level Pillar AoE can deal 952 damage to 4 targets for 364 total mana.  That's over 10 damage per mana used.  Our highest level Tears runs 690 Damage for 3-4 waves for 437 mana.  That's 4.7 to 6.3 Damage per mana.  And our highest level PBAoE...well, that's 648 DD to as many targets as your puller can pull and your enchanters can keep stun locked for the low, low cost of 342 mana.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As you can see, the Wizard class gets some pretty formidable AoE spells later in life.  The Column Line will be pretty effecient on 3+ targets starting at level 16, and you'll be using the level 34 Column (Circle of Force) as your soloing mainstay until 48th or so.  Your rain spells arn't effecient until your Tears line at 52, and you really are best to wait until 56th for your best AoE grouping capability.  (Pre 53, your PBAoEs arn't effecient.  At 53, Jyll's recast time is gonna slow down your ability to kill.  At 56, you can alternate your two Jyll's spells to very good effect, however.)<br>
<br>
Just kick back and have fun with them.  Making chit blow up is why you made a wizard, and AoEs make lots of chit blow up all at the same time.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Fun Fun!<br>
